HELLO I managed to survive my first week in school. if you ask me 'So how's school?', I would tell you, 'Its good AT THE MOMENT.'

haha when the assignments start piling up (actually they already did) and when those deadlines draw nearer and nearer, I think I would tell you, 'School sucks." lawls. I hate the fact that almost all the books that we need for assignments are reference books. being kiasu cheena peeps, they would rush to the library and grab hold of those books that can be borrowed once lesson ends. lyk wth. there are like 2000+ student teachers in the sch and yet they only have ard 2 copies each for those books. GREAT. and even for the public libraries, the books are ALL ON LOAN. so how on earth am I supposed to complete my assignments? and I dun see the point of buying the books cos all these modules are only for one sem! rawrs. 4 individual assignments and 3 group projects at the moment. lalalala. I think in the end I'll probably just hafta purchase those books, despite my rantings >< or mabbe I'll make a trip to national lib to try my luck.

still trying to adapt to sch life, as well as all those 2hr lectures/tutorials. 2hrs = VERY VERY LONG! had lessons from 1530 to 1930 on wed and my stomach was growling like nobody's business. but im glad my timetable isnt that sucky as compared to larry's timetable. he has 3 days with lessons ending at 1930 and also disgusting 6hr breaks before the next lesson starts. heng arh heng arh. most of my lessons start in the afternoon (so I can wake up late!) and end at a reasonable time. I simply love thursdays becos I only have 1 tutorial! :D but it would be even better if they could move this tutorial to some other day so my thursday would totally be free. okay besides that, I made some new friends from my tutorials! haha cihui, michelle etc etc. during ed psy II tut yesterday, we were told to draw sth that we like as part of the introduction and i drew my favourite doraemon and Ms Yang actually PRAISED ME FOR MY DRAWING. BWAHAHAS but I think my drawing sucks! funny. but anws, hope things get better along the way. and Im glad my sis is continuing her studies so I've someone to pei me! hehs. I shall read up on my lexicology notes ltr!

okay enough of school. went orchard with zhiyi yesterday. walked the whole of far east and half of 313. had my favourite fried mars bar and drank the kungfu milktea recommended by zhiyi and had a great chat with her! haha retail therapy rocks totally. I just love shopping, even if its just window shopping! :D:D sorry Im a shoppaa-horlicks (: and what's more, Im getting my pay soon! PAYDAY PAYDAY I LOVE PAYDAY. AND I GOT PAYRISE SIA!!!!! EGG-CITING. AND ZOMG HAHA i JUST SAW MY EXAM SCHEDULE! MY EXAM ENDS ON 10TH DEC! I thought my last day for sem one is 24th, but my exams end on 10th! WOOHOOOO EGG-CITING (X2) :D

oh oh I saw edwin in school ytd! hahah and he said if I need to borrow any assignments or notes, can always email him. actually, I shld request to go back northview for practicum so mabbe I'll get edwin as my CT. haha he's super duper nice. and 2 of the kids from northview primary actually talked to me on fb today and told me that they miss me. awwwws. haha so nice of them (: actually i kinda miss northview too. hahaha. aft all I was there for nearly a yr.

and I just got my hp bill. freaking sent ONE THOUSAND ONE HUNDRED AND FIFTEEN SMS LAST MONTH. nonsense. this must not continue. lol.

SYOG POST CELEB (yet again =p) TMR! :D:D:D

lastly, I just wna say, INTERNET I DISLIKE YOU! stop getting me d/c every 5mins or so, its plain irritating >:(

argh I spent my precious time typing the new post and yet lj freaking died on me >< rawrs am lazy to update so much right from the start so I shall just SUMMARISE wad I typed previously D:



kite flying is fun! we are so going to marina barrage again nxt fri to fly kites! :D

im currently enjoying my stone-at-home one week break! sometimes, even stoning at home makes me happy! haha that feeling of waking up as and when you like, not having to rush for work, rocks a million! so I must treasure this one week break.

going back northview ltr for teachers day celeb and also to have lunch with boonchun edwin sylvia xuanfeng larry! (:



I wna talk to you you you;

tsk im bored and sian. cos tmrs monday. rawrs I wna stone at home! fine, I shall not rant. five more days and then its goodbye.

holy shit la, I cant log in to nie portal! >< INCORRECT PASSWORD. but im lyk 99.9% sure that when i changed the nie password few weeks ago, I used the same old password that i've been using for other accounts. i've been trying like mad for the past 30min and I just cant log in. thought of other possible passwords that i might use but all dont work as well. and when i wanted to reset my password, they asked me for my old password. LIKE HELLO. isnt it clear that I wna reset password becos I forgot my old one? ._. crapshit if I cant log in, I cant get my timetable! and I need to go to sch just to reset my password becos they said they'll not entertain changing of password thru email or phone. oh come on, sucks. the more i think abt it, the more pekcek i get. moreover i haven even get my matric card, I cant go to sch to reset -.- so okay conclusion: wait for my sista to come back and hope that she can help me.

went for LEAN walk-a-jog today with my sister (: 9am at west coast park. and we freaking walked for 1hr plus, 5km. good exercise ehs. can walk away a lil of my fats HAHA. was sweating buckets under the hot sweltering sun but was quite fun, thou my sis kept complaining haha!


say hello to my sister! ((:


and then, say hello to the chickens! xD haha saw them near the toilets.

before I go and bathe,  i wna mention that I spent some $50 on the presents for the kids and chinese department. wad the fish.

Msg from BG Ishak Ismail -- To inspire global unity & instill national pride, your guys & girls from SSA have supported us to achieve that & mesmerized the world. Well done to ALL from SSA! Chairman Ng shared with me that IOC Pres Jacque said last night that he had watched 21 Opening Ceremonies & this one left him speechless & he then gave him a heartfelt hug which is uncharacteristic of him. All our local dignitaries have told me me to congratulate the team for the great show ie direct from PM, SM Goh, DPM & many other Ministers. I'm humble by all your people's passion & inspired by their spirit. Thanks also for the prayers.

SSA ROCKS!

AHHHH YOG IS OVER! having post-yog blues now haha. I'm already starting to miss everyone! ):

watched the repeat telecast just now and I cried! haha really touched aft watching. everything went off smoothly and the dragon looked damn beautiful! <3<3<3 WE DID IT, SSA! 

haha met zhiyi at tpy for breakfast and to write message for wilson yesterday before going tbsc to chant and also watch performances by trainers. thank you trainers! the bonamana dance was cool I LOVE IT HAHAHA. aft that we took bus to f1 pit. arrived there freaking early. 1.30pm. had our lunch and I must say, it tasted SO SO SO MUCH BETTER as compared to those previous dinners. last time eh, so they gave us something slightly better. lol I read the report on straits times abt volunteers complaining abt the food.  I AGREE! lol but still, the lunch was kinda oily. I didnt finish the food, as usual =p aft that we were all busy putting on makeup and camwhoring. wna say a big thank you to CALE for helping us with our makeup! I think fireflys really looked beautiful yesterday :D:D:D 

was raining in the afternoon and all of us were worried. thou the rain stopped but the dark clouds were still looming in the sky. all of us chanted while waiting and the clouds really disappeared aft some time. THE POWER OF DAIMOKU! <3 thank you gohonzon for the fine weather and great success of YOG!!! 

and guess what, I SAW MAO! HAHA. he was on duty at my light up point at the start :D was trying to look for him at gate 6 cos he told me he would be there. happy to see him hahaha but didnt get to take photo with him D:

so aft 5 months of training, everything ended. lol IM REALLY MISSING EVERYONE RIGHT NOW. happy that its a great victory, sad that it ended. thank you everyone who walked this syog journey along with me. really glad to know each and every one of you! thank you trainers (wilson, xyn, dixon, mike etc etc), SSA logistics (wouldnt noe wad to do without all of u! <3), SSA admin, SAF guys (LOL), WDs who chanted 6hrs for us yesterday and others who chanted for us too!, and most importantly, THANK YOU ALL THE PERFORMERS (ESP FIRE DANCERS FIREFLYS!) LOVE ALL OF YOU! thanks for making my 2010 a really memorable and great one. haha btw they were discussing abt the possibility of forming a SOKA FIRE GROUP. PLS FORM ONE SO ALL OF US CAN GATHER TGT AGAIN AND PERFORM FIRE! :D 

im counting down to 28th aug! POST PRODUCTION CELEBRATION <3
Wtf wtf! Sucks when u can't hear the alarm ring!!!

I SEE MYSELF HERE LOLS. the grp right in front. I think when u capture the perf with cam, the fire looks all the same even thou we are using different props. just balls of fire. and i've decided that its time to start taking photos! "The Singapore 2010 Youth Olympic Games Opening Ceremony will be a dazzling show of music and colour showcasing local talents and over 5,000 young performers. The spectacular opening show will be a treat for the senses with multimedia showcase, elaborate costumes, and bold performances with fire and water elements in the "Playing with Fire" and the "Reflecting Pool" performances." "105 performers from Bornfire and SOKA will be collaborating for the first time in the inaugural Youth Olympic Games Opening Ceremony. Bornfire is a non-profit organisation that supports fire and circus arts in the Asia region. They will be conducting and supporting the fire training of the SOKA youth volunteers in the show. The courageous SOKA youths have no prior experience in the field of fire arts and started training from scratch. They have been undergoing training since March 2010." :D:D:D

GROW HAIR GROW! anw went to ntu for talks yesterday the schs freaking big it took daddy quite some time to drive me to the destination. met up with charlotte! :D thou we only knew each other for like 2 days during tpp, we are quite close still hahaha. cant wait for sch to start man! CR2 ltr! mabbe will get to see michael there. hahaha. JIAYOU PPL! :D

im amazed (and disgusted) after looking at my knee. it looked okay to me on saturday. and then the blue-black became like outta control. rubbing/applying ointment/putting hot towel all do not seem to work at all! lol sorry I noe it looks DAMN ER but i feel the need to take a photo and post it here so I can laugh at myself in the future ._.

im waiting for 4pm. my eyes are closing i wna go home but its raininggggg. but anw watched shrek with guangyang and anna ytd. NICE! Im really going to doze off soon. in the midst of doing lesson ppt. 9periods tmr. save me man T.T AM LOOKING FORWARD TO SPLISH SPLASH ON THURS!

omg the torturous week ended! 1 down, 2 to go. 

it sucks to be shouting every time I enter a class, but I dun have a choice. I bet the kids are cursing and swearing in their hearts, but I feel like slapping them too everytime they do weird things instead of listening in class (e.g a boy cut his finger with a scissors, poke holes on his bottle cap and pour water on his hair and wadeva not. alot of dumb and weird things the kids can do that u cant imagine.)

and I think I must be super tired cos I slept all the way from 630pm ytd till 8am today, totally skipped my dinner. lol ._. sleeping is good (Y)

haix I'll be spending my weekend preparing for lessons and marking the never-ending piles of books T.T

hello world. freaking tired recently. busy with sch stuff and yog trngs. FIRE DANCE IS HARD HARD HARD. now theres one big blue-black on my knee, accompanied by 2 rather long cuts on the thigh. 

went out with pretty girl on fri. had my long-time-no-eat pizza hut! I'm always very full when I go out with osy. hahaha good appetite when you dine with pretty girl eh. and we actually watched KIDNAPPER. lawls but it was quite okay la, just a lil draggy, and having to shiver like shit cos it was freezing in the theatre. JUON NXT WEEK!!!!

haha omg I suddenly feel tempted to get Nokia X6 instead of waiting patiently for iphone 4g =.= first satio, then iphone, and now, X6. choosing btw x6 and iphone. AHHH which one shld I get! and shld I change my no.! D: 

(AND WHY IS YONA YONA PENGUIN ONLY SHOWING AT BISHAN VIVO PLAZASING TAMPINES AND TIONG BAHRU?!)

just came back after watching SYM. ROCKS TOTALLY. hahaha I cried thrice while watching. it portrayed the mentor-disciple spirit btw Toda Sensei and Ikeda Sensei and how both of them strive to build bridges of peace based on the life-affirming philosophy of Nichiren Buddhism. and the actors were really great! <3<3<3 wna watch it again but no more tickets for other show times liao. (the guy who acted as the young Ikeda Sensei is cute HAHA :D) THREE CHEERS FOR SSA AND YOUTH DIVISION! ^^

anyways, had my first (which was supposed to be the second) trng for YOG ytd. its seriously not easy to be a fire dancer. I think if I were to play with real fire, my hair would have been gone by now haha. really felt like giving up at first and just request to be the normal dancer. but I'm glad I didnt. shouldnt give up just becos it's harder than my previous performances. I will practise harder! :D really happy to be able to see junhao and minkit after so damn long! and knowing new friends like laurel and qijun (: hope the trngs will just get better and better! jiayou fire dancers!

(I should attempt to sleep soon cos I need to wake up in 7 hrs time D:) I hate meetings! cant I just get fever or sth?

OMG breakout was freaking NICE <3 I wna watch it again! haha 2 of the dancers are cute :D:D their dance was superb! AHHHHHH korean dancers are cool man. 

had olympia games yesterday in school and my house won!!! bwahaha it was quite surprising cos most of us thought that red house is unlikely to win. BUT WE WON! :D:D RED EAGLES! (haha reminds me of ARES!) but seriously I thought our dance was dumb. and I played quite a lot of games like shuttle run, tug-o-war, sit-ups, london bridge and wadeva not. now my whole body is aching.

yog at night. colleague's wedding and sym on sun. meeting till 330 on mon. AND THEN MY LONG AWAITED HOLS! omg one week is totally not enough, but better than nth.

and I'm PATIENTLY waiting for iphone 4g. when will it be out! D:

so chingay is finally over. haha I think I'll miss the trainings and the chatting sessions with my new friends! YOG is next! I just got the sms that I'm in for YOG perf too :D:D:D

and right now I'm having a friggin bad sorethroat (AGAIN) and random headache D:

happy cny (:

yay its going to be cny soon. HOLS HOLS HOLS xD looking forward to that!
